metadata.name: The Edge of Meaning #5
metadata.description:
Where sight ends, there is meaning, maybe. But maybe not something that we can understand. And maybe not something we can see.

AKA a couple of fragment shaders and a vertex shader roll terrain and reveal a message. The typeface is custom built for this series.

Press [spacebar] to toggle play/pause.

When paused, press [p] to create hi-res PNG.

metadata.name: Distant Points Of Weather #41
metadata.description:
The last leaves have fallen
The last vine has withered
While within these wombs
Dwell hosts of universes

Fractal galaxies emerge from the void
Behold the consummation
Bleeding from its aetherous wounds
Stretching beyond all time in a multidimensional genocide.

Project created using fractal art + code + chaos theory to generate unusual structures and geometries within fractals.

metadata.name: Radiant #148
metadata.description:
We were all born with a jewel in our heart – golden, shining.  Maybe you call it love, or the divine, or beauty.  The trials of life can cover up that jewel, and make it hard to see the beauty within.  We think we’re not worthy, not lovable.  But that’s a lie.  The jewel is always there.  You just need to clean off the gunk.  We are all made of love and supernovas.  You always were, and always will be - radiant.

Radiant was created generatively in p5.js.  Seven possible radial designs overlap on two canvases. On the top canvas, circles or arcs are erased to reveal the canvas below. There are four ways the background gets created, mostly using Perlin noise to pick colors from the palette. There are 34 hand-crafted palettes of 7 colors each. 

Original pixel density 1 with grain added automatically.
After pressing “open”:
2 – 5 to increase pixel density.  
g to add grain.  Adding grain takes a while at pixel density 5.
s to save a png.
Screen resize renders at pixel density 1.

I love sharing what I’ve learned about gen art and inspiring others on my YouTube channel, Steve’s Makerspace. Follow me there and on Twitter @stevemakerspace and Mastodon @stevesmakerspace.

metadata.name: Shine On #248
metadata.description:
You enter a room, bathed in light
Where a beautiful sculpture takes your sight
Shimmering in the glow of the sun
It's a sight to behold, it's simply won

Remember when you were young
You shone like the sun
Your radiance filled the room
With a feeling of pure bloom

Your heart sings, a soul takes flight
As you stand in awe, all worries take flight
Shine on you crazy diamond, bright and true
Your radiance fills the room, your heart anew

metadata.name: White Mountain Winter #44
metadata.description:
White Mountain Winter is collaboration between myself and the machine to describe scenes that are real, or were. Yet perhaps now foreign, or out of time, or far away. I provide the seed of a dream I remember, and trust the machine to help make it real again.

I grew up in a town much like some of these, homes dispersed throughout the valley beneath the shadows of the mountains rising around. This is a tribute to the memory of wintertime in that place; bleak, cold, grey, with the light seemingly always fading. Yet at the same time, the feeling of calm, solace, peace resonating through. Exposed to the mountain elements, yet protected by them. A delicate arrangement, but essential.

The seed of magic I remember is present in the experience of falling snow at dusk. Large flakes tumbling down and blanketing everything, no end in sight. The most striking thing is the silence. The fallen snow absorbing all distraction, insisting that your focus be sharpened to a singularity; right there, right then.

---
- Best rendered in Chrome browser (best performance, & canvas blur - please be patient :)
- Made with p5js
- Press "s" to save png

metadata.name: WHISPERS (in code) #392
metadata.description:
WHISPERS (in code) is part of the fx(hash) interactive minting experience at Performance in Code: Deciphering Value in Generative Art, Art Basel Miami Beach, 2022. 
The project is a collaborative performance between the viewer and AI. It reverses the usual approach of using AI as a tool to perform our intents (as in popular prompt-based AI methods) and gives the decision-making power to the AI, where we, humans, receive instructions on how to proceed in the creative process. Interaction happens in a multi-stage manner, in a metaphor for the process of training neural networks. At each step, after the user performs the action, they can send the image for evaluation by the neural network and receive another instruction (similarly to how networks learn by receiving feedback from the loss function).  What makes us different from the machines, however, is the presence of free will, and our ability to disobey the machine’s guidance. We are not restricted to its instructions and are free to interact with and break the artwork. 

Artwork is built on layers of photography, AI, GAN, diffusion, classification convolutional networks, random pixel manipulations, and user interaction. Like with most artist projects, it starts with a few memories, that are then re-imagined by GAN. The initial building blocks are a combination of photographs and AI outputs. The apparent lack of coherent subject choice in input images signifies how we build the perception of the world around us and apply an individual hierarchy to elements worth remembering. The blocks are then stripped of meaning by reducing them to abstract shapes and applying stochastic image transformations, guided by randomness. The neural network then learns to classify the images and outputs its best guesses on how to improve the pictures. 
 
The goal of the project is to explore the controversial question of authorship through the use of tools incorporating AI. Does it lie with decisive or executive power? Here, the boundaries are blurred and one can no longer distinguish the clear author of a finished artwork - is it the artist, AI, serendipity, or viewer? 


- Use your mouse to perform machine instructions.
- Use the "E" key to ask the neural network for instructions.
- Use the "R" key to reset the drawing.
- Use the "S" key to export an image.

metadata.name: Foundations #266
metadata.description:
In march of this year, I started working on a new series involving multi-layering, and overriding shapes. Drawing and playing with colors and opacity.
It started with squares and grid, it then involved deformations, and circles and other experimentations.
This path fits with my artistic generative approach: rather than having a completely predefined idea, I start with a simple concept that evolves during creation. Then surprises happened, and I embraced them.

But this year was not like any other: 2022 has gifted me with a new birthday, the one of my son.

Over the past twelve months, I’ve watched him discovering the world surrounding him, learning and trying new things, laughing, or getting frustrated, sad or happy…
While learning to become a parent, I’ve been in an introspection phase where I questioned what it means to be “a father”. What impact will I have on my son, consciously or not?

“Foundations” takes shape in this context: 2 humans trying and exploring while being inspired by each other.
This series is a first of a set of at least 3, that illustrates an idea of what is an “Identity”, and what makes us who we are.

The foundations of an identity are laid in the first days of a child’s life. They will be influenced by many factors; including parenting, cultural environment, life experiences… 
Of course, as humans we are in constant evolution; life happens, sometimes for the best, sometimes for the worst, and our personality will be impacted…
But this will be a topic for another time. 


Today, we are at the start.

metadata.name: Flowers #75
metadata.description:
This project is inspired by natural flowers.
Flowers and foliage in the piece are arranged randomly, but they follow a regular pattern, as flowers do as they grow.
Initially, flowers are produced randomly and without color. Afterwards, the pieces are painted according to the color palettes, so that viewers can feel the effect of colors.
Each piece is processed until the frame part is reached.

Fully generated by p5.js

Press 's' to get a 3000x3000 px PNG file.

metadata.name: Metal Waves #24
metadata.description:
The generative arts help us to make the hardest metals and shape them to our liking. When large objects are broken into smaller pieces, flexibility increases, and the smaller the pieces, the more creative you become.
This work comprises thousend of lines made up of hundreds of points arranged in the same direction, waves made up of thousands of lines, and pieces made of dozens of waves.
Considering all the starting and ending points of these waves on the circumference of a circle is perhaps the most challenging part, In order to yield something like a round art board.

You can order a piece in any size and color if you are one of the owners. On Twitter, DM your custom size and colors. 
Made by p5.js

press 's' to save original size

metadata.name: The Past Ahead #112
metadata.description:
Cyanotypes once were the most advanced technology to create images. When I see one today I look at it as a beautiful relic and I can't help but put my present in perspective. In these uncertain times the technologies we use to create are threatened with sudden extinction. But I feel joy in imagining our works joining the strata of history, a fallen species, the breeding ground of creations to come.

Controls :

• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

The Past Ahead by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: FAT Christmas #194
metadata.description:
“FAT Christmas” 由三位台灣創作者主導，並且與另外幾位創作者共創部件。包含發行過 Moonlight Impression 的 mido、影像創作者 Graphyni、熱衷 AI 生成的 Fagem。
你可以在這個生成器中獲取 Chang Ming Yao 的 Aka’s Ape 或由 Chi.L 繪製的 AKAZOO Cat，甚至是 roupin_art 的 Dino Ali。
並祝福所有 Tezos 的創作者與藏家，接下來一年能充滿希望。

我們竭盡所能的補充多樣性，確保每次鑄造都是明確且獨特的結果。
在30多種的背景中，包含由創作者提供的特殊款式，如果你足夠幸運，將有機會獲得美麗且獨特的角色 。

角色方面：
Aka’s Ape 包含 8 種 character、8 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、3 種 personality。
Aka Zoo Cat 包含 7 種 character、10 種 eyes、7 種 mouth、5 種  personality。
Dino Ali 包含 26 種 character、5 種 eyes、8 種 mouth、6 種 personality。
所有角色共享超過 20 款頭飾、9 款服裝、10 種服裝印花。
角色前方桌面的三個位置，亦各自包含 10 種以上的配件。

由衷的希望各位都能玩得開心。
祝大家聖誕快樂，新年快樂。

“FAT Christmas” is a collabration of three creators from Taiwan, with parts contributed by creators including mido's “Moonlight Impression”, video creator Graphyni and generative AI enthusiast Fagem.
You can get Aka’s Ape by Chang Ming Yao, AKAZOO  Cat by Chi.L and Dino Ali by roupin_art from the generator.
Blessing to all Tezos creators and collectors, filled with hope in the coming year.

Diversity is replenished in our best effort to ensure apparent and unique results in every mint.
Among over 30 different backgrounds, including special design provided by the creators, you will have a chance to get a gorgeous and unique character if you are lucky enough.

About the characters:
Aka’s Ape includes 8 types of character, 8 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 3 types of personality.
Aka Zoo Cat includes 7 types of character, 10 types of eyes, 7 types of mouth and 5 types of personality.
Dino Ali includes 26 types of character, 5 types of eyes, 8 types of mouth and 6 types of personality.
All characters share over 20 headwears, 9 clothes and 10 clothes patterns.
Over 10 decorations will be assigned to 3 positions on the table in front of the character.

Sincerely hope everyone can have fun.
And wishing you all a Merry Christmas and a happy new year.

metadata.name: Haste Season #3
metadata.description:
“Do not spoil the wonder with haste.”
― J.R.R. Tolkien, The Return of the King

This piece is here to point us to the fact that Haste season is upon us. It is the season when more people are moving than usual, and the dynamic movement of each person gives our world a wonderful composition. But it also increases the chance that something really bad will happen. Let's ensure that the chaotic image of cities, crowds, and haste that is before us becomes the perfect image of chaos. Image of people who love and respect one another. Image of wonder that we can be.

Made with P5js.
Bajiru, December 2022.
